<span class=pageheading>Hidden Home Defects to Watch For</SPAN><br><br>



<p class="text">No home is flawless, but certain physical problems can be
expensive. Watch for:</p>


<ol style='margin-top:0in' start=1 type=1>
 <li class="text" style='mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in'><b>Water
     leaks</b>. Look for stains on ceilings and near the baseboards, especially
     in basements or attics.<br style='mso-special-character:line-break'>
     <![if !supportLineBreakNewLine]><br style='mso-special-character:line-break'>
     <![endif]></li>
 <li class="text" style='mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in'><b>Shifting
     foundations</b>. Look for large cracks along the home’s foundation.<br
     style='mso-special-character:line-break'>
     <![if !supportLineBreakNewLine]><br style='mso-special-character:line-break'>
     <![endif]></li>
 <li class="text" style='mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in'><b>Drainage</b>.
     Look for standing water, either around the foundation of the home of in
     the yard.<br style='mso-special-character:line-break'>
     <![if !supportLineBreakNewLine]><br style='mso-special-character:line-break'>
     <![endif]></li>
 <li class="text" style='mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in'><b>Termites</b>.
     Look for weakened or grooved wood, especially near ground level.<br
     style='mso-special-character:line-break'>
     <![if !supportLineBreakNewLine]><br style='mso-special-character:line-break'>
     <![endif]></li>
 <li class="text" style='mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in'><b>Worn
     roofs</b>. Look for broken or missing copings and buckled shingles as well
     as water spots on ceilings.<br style='mso-special-character:line-break'>
     <![if !supportLineBreakNewLine]><br style='mso-special-character:line-break'>
     <![endif]></li>
 <li class="text" style='mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in'><b>Inadequate
     wiring</b>. Look for antiquated fuse boxes, extension cords (indicating
     insufficient outlets), and outlets without a place to plug in the
     grounding prong.<br style='mso-special-character:line-break'>
     <![if !supportLineBreakNewLine]><br style='mso-special-character:line-break'>
     <![endif]></li>
 <li class="text" style='mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in'><b>Plumbing
     problems.</b> Very low water pressure, banging in pipes.</li>
</ol>

